# 020 Knowledge Evolution Engine

**Version:** 1.0  
**Status:** Vision  
**Last Updated:** 2026-07-09

---

# 1. Purpose

This document defines the Knowledge Evolution Engine of RISEN.

The purpose of the Knowledge Evolution Engine is to continuously improve knowledge through accumulated observations.

Knowledge is not static.

Knowledge grows through observation.

---

# 2. Philosophy

Traditional systems assume knowledge is predefined.

RISEN assumes knowledge evolves.

```text
Observation

↓

Knowledge

↓

New Observation

↓

Refined Knowledge
```

Knowledge is continuously enriched by real-world care.

---

# 3. Why Knowledge Evolves

Care environments constantly change.

Every day professionals discover

- new patterns
- new interventions
- new relationships
- new behaviors

RISEN should learn from these discoveries.

---

# 4. Sources of Knowledge Evolution

Knowledge evolves from

- repeated observations
- repeated episodes
- recurring trajectories
- intervention outcomes
- professional feedback
- AI-supported pattern discovery

No single observation changes knowledge.

Evidence accumulates over time.

---

# 5. Evolution Process

```text
Observation

↓

Knowledge

↓

Episode

↓

Pattern

↓

Trajectory

↓

Outcome

↓

Knowledge Evolution
```

Knowledge improves continuously.

---

# 6. Types of Knowledge

RISEN manages several kinds of knowledge.

## Clinical Knowledge

Medical and nursing concepts.

---

## Care Knowledge

Daily care practices.

---

## Behavioral Knowledge

Observed behavioral patterns.

---

## Environmental Knowledge

Relationships with surroundings.

---

## Intervention Knowledge

Effects of professional care.

---

## Organizational Knowledge

Knowledge unique to each care organization.

---

# 7. AI's Role

AI does not create truth.

AI suggests hypotheses.

Professionals validate them.

```text
Observation

↓

Pattern

↓

AI Hypothesis

↓

Professional Review

↓

Knowledge
```

Knowledge grows through collaboration.

---

# 8. Knowledge Confidence

Every knowledge element has confidence.

Confidence increases through

- repeated evidence
- multiple users
- multiple episodes
- intervention success

Confidence decreases when evidence becomes inconsistent.

---

# 9. Knowledge Graph Evolution

The Knowledge Graph is dynamic.

Nodes may

- grow
- merge
- split
- gain confidence
- lose confidence

Relationships may strengthen or weaken over time.

---

# 10. Organizational Learning

RISEN enables organizations to learn.

```text
One Observation

↓

Many Observations

↓

Shared Knowledge

↓

Better Care
```

Knowledge belongs to the organization.

Not to AI alone.

---

# 11. Explainability

Every evolved knowledge item must explain

- supporting observations
- supporting episodes
- supporting trajectories
- confidence
- evolution history

Knowledge must remain transparent.

